This paper deals with information theoretic aspects of secure communication, specifically in the context of broadcast channels with confidential messages. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also discusses the security aspects of the communication, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The use of coding schemes and error probability analysis suggests that it could also belong to cs.SI (Signal Processing), cs.MM (Multimedia), or cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture).
